<beginCreatedObjects>
<beginStartingNarrative>
This game addresses estimation adjustment based on effort drivers not related 
to the software product itself.

CONTEXT

You have already performed an initial effort estimation based on Non-Functional 
Requirements (NFR). Now you must refine this estimation by incorporating 10 
additional effort drivers that reflect project context beyond the software 
product itself.

These drivers come from Boehm's COCOMO model and include:
  • Computer Attributes: TIME, STOR, TURN
  • Personnel Attributes: ACAP, AEXP, PCAP, LEXP
  • Project Attributes: MODP, TOOL, SCED

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

YOUR TASK

For each scenario:
1. Review your initial NFR estimation (Range 1-5)
2. Count the levels of the 10 effort drivers
3. Calculate total weight: Low=-1, Nominal=0, High=+1, Very High=+2
4. Apply adjustment criteria based on total weight
5. Select adjusted estimation position (1-12)

ESTIMATION POSITIONS
  • 1-8: Half-intervals (bottom/top of each range) for precise adjustment
  • 9-12: Full ranges (entire range) for broader adjustment

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ESTIMATION POSITIONS (1-12)

Half-intervals (precise adjustment):
  1. Range 1 - Bottom half
  2. Range 1 - Top half
  3. Range 2 - Bottom half
  4. Range 2 - Top half
  5. Range 4 - Bottom half
  6. Range 4 - Top half
  7. Range 5 - Bottom half
  8. Range 5 - Top half

Full ranges (broader adjustment):
  9. Range 1 (entire)
 10. Range 2 (entire)
 11. Range 4 (entire)
 12. Range 5 (entire)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INTERACTIVE TOOL

Use the online questionnaire for step-by-step calculations and visual selection:

https://chairegestionproduitsprojetslogiciels.github.io/simse-software-estimation-capability/questionnaires/game-4-questionnaire.html


================================================================================
<endStartingNarrative>
